what is the plural for mouse when referring to more than one mouse that you use on the computer would it also be referred to as computer mice that is a hotly debated issue in the it arena while common logics says it should be mice not all techs agree there are several online dictionaries of computer terms which give mouse as the correct term it was enough of an issue that we settled in my group by using meeses instead of either mouse or mice English plural Mouse (computing) Mouse IMac Apple Computer Acronym and initialism Logic Grammatical number Copyright Computer and video games X Window System Church of Christ Model (abstract) Plural of virus Douglas Engelbart Computer virus Dutch language Inflection WIMP (computing) Mathematics Internet slang Swedish language Source port Rhyme Jef Raskin Computer numbering formats American and British English differences Esperanto grammar Cheating in Counter-Strike RS-232 Philosophy The Matrix character names G__del's incompleteness theorem Intelligent design Ontology (computer science) Computer software Sega Dreamcast Economics Computer Quantum computer Democracy Mathematical logic Software testing German language IBM Psychoanalysis Patent At sign Opera (web browser) User interface Windows 2000 Linguistics Computer security Mighty Mouse Minesweeper (computer game) Intelligent dance music PlayStation 2 Computer-supported collaboration Computer and video game genres First-person shooter Universal Serial Bus Spyware Crossword Physics Central processing unit Server Chinese language This Week in Tech House Mouse Association for Computing Machinery Of Mice and Men Mouse gesture Recording Industry Association of America Computer science Ebook Cult Stardock Bulgarian language Bob McEwen Computer storage Prior probability German spelling reform of 1996 Consensus Microsoft Computer program Censorship in Australia City of Heroes Copyleft Gender-neutral language Aspartame Grammar Tablet PC Tolkien fandom Graphical user interface Condorcet 